<section id="overview" class="py-20 border-b border-gray-100 scroll-mt-8">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-3">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-400 mb-8">
      01 â€” Overview
    </h2>
    <div class="grid gap-0 sm:grid-cols-2 [&>div]:py-6 [&>div]:pr-6 [&>div:nth-child(even)]:pl-6">
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">TypeScript with WebAssembly</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Uses WASM for layouts, font rendering, glyphs and SVGs. Everything else is TypeScript.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Cross-platform</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Runs on macOS and web. Write your TypeScript once, and it runs on a browser or macOS with no modifications.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Native WebGPU</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Uses Google's Dawn implementation of WebGPU when building for native.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Static binary builds</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Compiles JavaScript to single statically executable binary using Bun's FFI and file embedding.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Font rendering</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Full-featured font rendering using rustybuzz (Rust implementation of harfbuzz) for full TTF rendering. Uses Noto Color Emoji by default, with font fallback support.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Elements and components</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Elements like divs, text, and links. Also buttons, tooltips, tabs, scrollbars, dialogs, images, checkboxes, radios, toggles, and more.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Tailwind-style utilities</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Style elements and components using Tailwind-like utilities directly on the elements and components.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Text editing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Text editing works out of the box. Cross-element selection, text input, range selection, select-all, and copy-and-paste via clipboard APIs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">SVG rendering</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Renders SVGs fairly well. Vector graphics support for scalable, crisp visuals at any resolution.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Flexbox and grids</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Full flexbox support, and CSS-grid-like features via the Taffy library.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-gray-900">Custom cursors</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Pointers, text, default, and more. Basically, anything you can do with Tailwind's cursor classes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
